20/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania received average ratings on performance and competitiveness in a report assessing the country's progress in meeting the EU's Lisbon Agenda. The report, published on Monday (19 April) by the British Embassy in Bucharest, was drafted by the Applied Economics Group of the Romanian Economics Society. It found that Romania ranks low in innovation and research compared to other European countries, but has a competitive edge in information technology. (Rompres - 19/04/04)
